monstrous sexuality in the wake of the French Revolution, the bourgeoisie weaponized both sexual constraint and sexual freedom in order to produce and control a reliable and regimented labor class and subordinate it to civil society and the state. Only by grasping sexuality as a field of social contention and the site of class conflict, Chitty contends, can we embark on a politics that destroys sexuality as a tool and effect of power, and open a front against the forces that keep us unfree.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 26. Mai 2021) 0aCapitalismxSocial aspects. 0aHomosexualityxPolitical aspects. 0aMarxian economics. 0aPhilosophy, Marxist. 0aQueer theory. 0aSocialist feminism. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / LGBT Studies / Gay Studies.2bisacsh1 aFox, Max, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aFox, Max, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aNealon, Christopher, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aNealon, Christopher.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDUP Frontlist eBook-Package 2020z978311069631808iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2020 Englishz978311070471608iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2020z9783110704518oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Social Sciences 2020 Englishz978311070472308iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Sociology, Education, Psychology 2020z9783110704549oZDB-23-SEW40uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9781478012238zCo-access DOI >> click Walter de Gruyter40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781478012238423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9781478012238.jpg  a978-3-11-069631-8  DUP Frontlist eBook-Package 2020b2020  a978-3-11-070471-6  EBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 